route: text

---

[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Check out this 24K 360 photo. Now compare&nbsp; it to the Insta360 X5, the DJI Osmo 360,&nbsp;&nbsp; and the professional Canon R5 Mark II with the new&nbsp; RF fisheye lens. All shooting the exact same room.&nbsp;'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'If you are selling a property&nbsp; worth several million dollars,&nbsp;&nbsp; do you show a buyer this&nbsp; virtual tour, or this one?&nbsp;'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'In this independent review, I will show you what&nbsp; this mystery camera can do, and why you should,&nbsp;&nbsp; or should not, upgrade. If you are still shooting high-end listings&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'on a consumer 360 camera like this? You&nbsp; are losing clients to someone who is&nbsp;&nbsp; not. Let me show you what they use, and&nbsp; how they do more listings in less time. So this is the Realsee Galois P4 3D laser&nbsp; scanner. And it is not just a 360 camera. It is&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'an all-in-one virtual tour robot. One tap on the back of the camera,&nbsp;&nbsp; and it scans the entire 360 environment, without&nbsp; needing a phone. Out comes a 24K 360 panorama,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a high-density point cloud, a 3D dollhouse, and&nbsp; a floor plan with accurate measurements. All the&nbsp;&nbsp; professional assets a standard virtual&nbsp; tour needs, without manual recreation.&nbsp;'

[01:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'It is the latest upgrade of the Realsee&nbsp; Galois M2, which I reviewed here.&nbsp; Realsee is a Matterport alternative. And&nbsp; with the P4, I will go further. This is&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'now a Leica BLK360 laser scanner alternative.&nbsp; And now you can even use it on a movie set.&nbsp; In my older review, you already saw the&nbsp; Galois M2 completely destroy Matterport&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in terms of quality. And Matterport is getting&nbsp; even more greedy these days. Back in May 2025,&nbsp;&nbsp; right after the CoStar acquisition, they&nbsp; raised their subscription prices again,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in the name of AI. In a declining commercial&nbsp; real estate market, that is just not okay.&nbsp; So if you already made the switch to&nbsp; Realsee, the real question is this.&nbsp;&nbsp; What does upgrading from the M2 to the P4&nbsp; actually buy you? Let us take a closer look.'

[02:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The key differences are scanning&nbsp; range, scanning speed, LiDAR accuracy,&nbsp;&nbsp; and the resolution of the final 360 photo. For a virtual tour camera, image quality&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'matters most. On the left we have the P4, on&nbsp; the right the M2. Punch in on a focus chart&nbsp;&nbsp; 10 feet away at 300%, or 3X zoom, and they&nbsp; look mostly the same. The P4 has slightly&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[02:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'better color accuracy and less noise, thanks to&nbsp; its new multispectral HDR technology. But punch&nbsp;&nbsp; in on something far in the distance, and now the&nbsp; gap shows up. That is the P4\'s 8 times lossless&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'zoom and 300-megapixel panorama at work, more than&nbsp; double the M2 and the Matterport Pro3, both only&nbsp;&nbsp; at 134MP. Look at the pipe on the side of the&nbsp; house. In the M2 result, it is completely gone.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'That is a big deal if you do site surveys. Any&nbsp; contractor or AEC pro knows exactly what I mean. With its new 100-meter LiDAR range, up from&nbsp; 25 meters on the M2 and finally matching the&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Matterport Pro3, the P4 can cover the same&nbsp; space in fewer scan positions, or capture&nbsp;&nbsp; large outdoor locations that were never possible&nbsp; before. It also pulls a far denser point cloud,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[03:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'around 125,000 points per second against&nbsp; only 18,000 on the M2 and 100,000 on the&nbsp;&nbsp; Pro3. The P4 is really aimed at commercial real&nbsp; estate, where size and accuracy both matter.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Its sub-10-millimeter accuracy is about&nbsp; twice as precise as the M2 or the Pro3. But, I have to call it out. It is still&nbsp; less accurate than the Leica BLK360 G2,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'which hits only 4 millimeters at 10 meters. Scanning speed is another big decision&nbsp; factor for virtual tour capture. And it&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'seems to be the only advantage a one-shot&nbsp; 360 camera like the Insta360 X5 has,&nbsp;&nbsp; besides price. Most of the time, you need to&nbsp; move fast and cover a large number of properties.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'You are paying the operator by the hour, and&nbsp; labor costs more than the camera ever will.&nbsp; Here is the side-by-side capture speed comparison.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[04:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The Galois P4 takes 18 seconds to finish a full&nbsp; scan. Not 16 seconds, like the spec sheet and some&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[05:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'influencers claimed. But still really fast.&nbsp; The Galois M2 takes 31 seconds on the latest&nbsp;&nbsp; firmware. Almost double the time per point. Now,&nbsp; most people assume a one-shot 360 camera like the&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[05:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Insta360 X5 will be faster. It is not. It took&nbsp; the X5 almost 55 seconds to finish a 7-bracket&nbsp;&nbsp; HDR capture. More than three times longer than&nbsp; the Galois P4. And the DSLR is fully manual,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[05:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'so it makes sense it took the longest, over&nbsp; a minute per location. So if time is money,&nbsp;&nbsp; the Galois P4 will save you a lot of it. But hold on. Not quite. This is an independent&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[05:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'review, so I am not going to just tell you what&nbsp; the spec sheet says. The Galois P4 actually has&nbsp;&nbsp; two capture modes. Standard, and High Quality.&nbsp; Let us do a quick comparison. The High Quality&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[06:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'mode has less digital noise and fewer aliasing&nbsp; artifacts. And if you zoom into distant details,&nbsp;&nbsp; High Quality holds more than the Standard mode.&nbsp; Since you spent thousands on a professional&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[06:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'camera, you will want High Quality mode to&nbsp; squeeze out every bit of detail. So High&nbsp;&nbsp; Quality should be the only mode you use. But here is the catch. You can not enable&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[06:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'High Quality from the touchscreen, or from&nbsp; that heavily advertised Blind Capture mode.&nbsp;&nbsp; You have to turn it on by tapping the gear icon&nbsp; in the mobile app and setting it to High Quality,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[06:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'like so. It is not on by default. So even though&nbsp; the Galois P4 can be operated without connecting&nbsp;&nbsp; to a phone, we do not recommend that workflow. It&nbsp; is not worth sacrificing quality for convenience.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[07:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Not to mention the capture mistakes you will make&nbsp; without reviewing each scan. Coming back later to&nbsp;&nbsp; rescan and add missing points will always cost&nbsp; you more than doing a perfect job in one go.'

[07:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Your clients pay for the highest quality of&nbsp; service. Give them the highest quality output.&nbsp;&nbsp; There is a reason we get hired by Fortune 500&nbsp; companies to build educational virtual tours&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[07:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'around the world. Because we pay attention&nbsp; to detail and give clients our best. I hope&nbsp;&nbsp; I can pass that same mentality and work&nbsp; ethic on to you. Strive for the best,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[07:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'not mediocrity. Raise the bar for&nbsp; the entire virtual tour industry. Luckily, even in High Quality mode, the&nbsp; Galois P4 only took 23 seconds to finish&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[08:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a single capture. Still well under the&nbsp; M2, and every other solution out there.&nbsp;&nbsp; If you watched my Galois M2 review here, you&nbsp; know the DSLR still beat the M2. So how does it&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[08:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'compare to the P4, especially with the latest and&nbsp; most expensive fisheye lens, the Canon RF 7-14mm?&nbsp; From left to right, we have the Insta360&nbsp; X5 HDR, the Galois P4, the DJI Osmo 360,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[08:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and the Canon R5 Mark II with the RF 7-14mm&nbsp; fisheye. The X5 is full of chromatic aberration.&nbsp;&nbsp; Really bad for a virtual tour. Just do not use&nbsp; it. It drags down the quality of our entire&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[08:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'industry. Even though the Realsee platform&nbsp; technically supports every Insta360 camera,&nbsp;&nbsp; this is not the one to use. The DJI Osmo 360 and&nbsp; its 120-megapixel photo is not bad for a virtual&nbsp;&nbsp; tour, but it suffers some color loss, as you can&nbsp; see here. Comparing the Galois P4 to the Canon,&nbsp;&nbsp; the P4 is the clear winner on close-up detail&nbsp; with that impressive 8 time lossless zoom.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[09:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And even on chromatic aberration, where&nbsp; the new Canon fisheye is great for that,&nbsp;&nbsp; the P4 still comes closest to reality. So officially, the Galois P4 is the best&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[09:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '360 virtual tour camera out there. You&nbsp; can still shoot a gigapixel panorama on&nbsp;&nbsp; a DSLR with a zoom lens and beat it on pure&nbsp; image quality. But then the post-production&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[09:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'complexity just does not make sense for the&nbsp; amount of money you get paid these days. But again, this is an honest review. And there is&nbsp; a big design drawback to the Galois series. It is&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[09:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'missing the top. We do not care about the bottom,&nbsp; since that is just the tripod. But the top could&nbsp;&nbsp; be something incredible, like Michelangelo\'s&nbsp; Creation of Adam on the Sistine Chapel ceiling.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[10:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'That is where the immersion breaks. The P4&nbsp; captures 145 degrees of vertical coverage,&nbsp;&nbsp; 10 degrees more than the M2. But it is&nbsp; still not the full sphere you get from&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[10:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a DSLR or an Insta360 rig. The Realsee&nbsp; platform uses AI to patch that hole. You&nbsp;&nbsp; can see it in the 360 panorama you download&nbsp; through the add-on features. But it is AI,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[10:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'not reality. And the RAW image you&nbsp; download comes without that AI fill.&nbsp;&nbsp; So this is something you need to consider,&nbsp; and something other reviews barely mention. So if you are like me, chasing the&nbsp; absolute best quality virtual tour,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[10:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the Galois P4 is the ARRI Alexa or the Sony&nbsp; Venice 2 of the virtual tour world. It is&nbsp;&nbsp; worth every penny if quality matters to you. Not only that, Realsee lets you download the&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[11:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'original RAW DNG file, right here under&nbsp; Add-ons, RAW file. It costs 15 credits,&nbsp;&nbsp; roughly 40 to 45 dollars. Pretty pricey. But&nbsp; you can grade that RAW DNG to get a polished,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[11:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'magazine-quality look, close to what you&nbsp; would pull from a high-end Canon or Sony&nbsp;&nbsp; mirrorless. Use Photoshop\'s AI to patch the top&nbsp; and bottom, like so, for a fully immersive 360,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[11:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'with the rich color depth of a true RAW file. So&nbsp; for the very high-end clients who want to host the&nbsp;&nbsp; tour on 3DVista or krpano, you can absolutely&nbsp; do it with these high-quality DNG RAW files.'

[11:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I do not think the Galois P4 makes as much sense&nbsp; if you skip the Realsee platform for hosting&nbsp;&nbsp; entirely. But here is the thing. You can if you&nbsp; want. You can use the Galois P4 as a very high-end&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[11:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '360 camera without Realsee hosting. It is not&nbsp; like Matterport, which tries to own your captures.&nbsp; And by the way, downloading the 24K JPG panorama&nbsp; is only 5 credits, roughly 10 dollars. It still&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[12:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'has that same impressive high-resolution clarity,&nbsp; and it is a ready-to-post 360 photo package. So&nbsp;&nbsp; if you need to post the pano to Facebook&nbsp; 360 for marketing, or to Zillow 3D Home&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[12:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for extra listings, you can, and it will not&nbsp; break the bank. Ten dollars is just two cups&nbsp;&nbsp; of coffee in Los Angeles, and the marketing reach&nbsp; on Zillow and the other MLS listings is worth it.'

[12:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And here is the kicker. Since October 2025,&nbsp; Zillow stopped embedding Matterport tours,&nbsp;&nbsp; after CoStar did not renew the API agreement.&nbsp; So there is really no reason to pay for the&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[12:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'expensive Matterport anymore. Switching&nbsp; to Realsee will save you so much more&nbsp;&nbsp; money. A company that has no interest&nbsp; in owning your tour, or your business.'

[13:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'There are also some nice quality-of-life&nbsp; updates. The P4 now runs an NVIDIA Jetson&nbsp;&nbsp; Orin Nano, the same class of AI&nbsp; computer you find inside robots.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[13:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'That is why it can stitch a 300-megapixel&nbsp; panorama, merge the multispectral HDR,&nbsp;&nbsp; and process the point cloud right&nbsp; on the camera, almost instantly.'

[13:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'It comes with a Made-in-Italy&nbsp; Manfrotto MT190CX tripod,&nbsp;&nbsp; with a quick-release design that speeds up&nbsp; capture on site while keeping everything&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[13:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'rock steady. You also get a high-quality carrying&nbsp; bag and extra batteries for long capture days.&nbsp;&nbsp; Everything just feels premium and professional,&nbsp; not the cheap plastic of a consumer 360 camera. Yes, it is expensive. But it is&nbsp; well thought out and ready to go,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[14:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'with no extra accessories&nbsp; needed besides your phone. Here is my honest verdict. If you already own&nbsp; the Galois M2, I do not think you should run out&nbsp;&nbsp; and spend another seven thousand dollars on the&nbsp; P4. Unless you are like me, a perfectionist who&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[14:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'always wants to give clients the absolute best.&nbsp; But if you do not have a Galois yet, and you are&nbsp;&nbsp; looking for an all-in-one virtual tour platform&nbsp; that can generate floor plans, a 3D dollhouse,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[14:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'PLY point cloud files you can feed into a&nbsp; Gaussian Splatting workflow for Apple Vision Pro,&nbsp;&nbsp; plus 3D models and CAD files, then right now&nbsp; might be a good time to grab a used M2. People&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[14:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'are about to sell their M2 at a big discount to&nbsp; upgrade to the P4, after they see this video. But I want to take a step back&nbsp; and expand your mind a little.&nbsp;'

[15:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This kind of technology is not&nbsp; just for commercial real estate,&nbsp;&nbsp; which is a brutal, low-margin business these&nbsp; days. LiDAR scanners and high-definition 360&nbsp;&nbsp; cameras are quietly becoming tools&nbsp; for the film industry as well.'

[15:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Here is what they unlock. Location Scouting -&nbsp; walk a real place before you ever fly there,&nbsp;&nbsp; inside an XR headset like Apple&nbsp; Vision Pro. Previsualization,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[15:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'plan your camera moves and lighting&nbsp; inside the 3D scan. Virtual set design,&nbsp;&nbsp; build and dress the set digitally for director&nbsp; approval. VFX support, scan the set before&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[15:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the camera rolls so the digital effects line up&nbsp; exactly with the footage. Set extension, turn one&nbsp;&nbsp; corner of a room into an entire palace, digitally. And the big one. Environment creation and virtual&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[15:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'production. Put your scanned world on a giant&nbsp; LED wall, and your actors perform inside it,&nbsp;&nbsp; lit by it with image base lighting,&nbsp; without ever leaving the stage.'

[16:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'That is the workflow. Scan a&nbsp; real location into a point cloud,&nbsp;&nbsp; capture a high dynamic range image to&nbsp; light it, rebuild it in Unreal Engine,&nbsp;&nbsp; and shoot your scene inside it. Location&nbsp; scouting, set reconstruction, and lighting all&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[16:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'collapse into one digital pipeline. Real-world&nbsp; capture, rebuilt and relit inside a 3D engine. And here is the part that should get you&nbsp; thinking. All of this used to need a full&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[16:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'technical crew and laser scanning&nbsp; gear that costs more than a car.&nbsp;&nbsp; Technology like the P4 now puts that same&nbsp; high-resolution capture in a backpack,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[16:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for seven thousand dollars. The gap between a solo&nbsp; creator and a Hollywood pipeline is closing fast. So stop thinking of this as just a&nbsp; Virtual Tour camera. Think of it as&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[17:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a key. A way into the same workflows the&nbsp; biggest Hollywood productions are using.&nbsp; And this is the kind of future-focused VFX&nbsp; that really excites me. Not the generative&nbsp;&nbsp; AI slop trying to take over our industry.&nbsp; You can use the Galois P4 and other Realsee&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[17:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'technology to capture the data that feeds&nbsp; into photogrammetry, 3D reconstruction,&nbsp;&nbsp; and Gaussian Splatting workflows. If that&nbsp; interests you, do not forget to subscribe, and we&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[17:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'will keep pushing the industry forward with bold,&nbsp; creative thinking, together. Ciao, my friend.'
